===Transitive verb===
'''to smash''' ('''smashing''', '''smashed''')

<!-- same as "break violently?#To damage or destroy something brittle by strong, blunt pressure.
#:''The demolotion team smashed the buildings to rubble.''-->
#To break (something brittle) violently.
#:''The flying rock smashed the window to pieces.''
#To hit extremely hard.
#:''Bonds smashed the ball 467 feet, the second longest home run in the history of the park.''
#(''figuratively'') To ruin completely and suddenly.
#:''The news smashed any hopes of a reunion.''
#(''figuratively'') To defeat [[overwhelming]]ly.
#:''The Indians smashed the Yankees 22-0.''

